			 I was still in bed inside the motorhome.
			 All windows were closed, yet rain was dripping onto my face. 
			 Damn!
			 Well, I found another towel, stuffed it into the dripping gap, turned over, and tried to sleep some more.
			 An hour and a half later, the night was finally over. </p>
		<p> Since three towels were now completely soaked, we decided to get an early start and drive to Cairns.
			First, it shouldn't rain there, and second, the Hippie Camper branch in Cairns is where we're supposed to return the motorhome in 8 days. </p>
		<p> On the way there, we made a list of all the defects we noticed in this motorhome.
			From wipers that are so hard you could use them as a saw, to the nasty smell of cat urine that regularly wafts through the car and seemed even worse today. </p>
