        <p> Around noon we arrived at Hippie Camper and had to wait until an apprentice took care of us. 
			After we explained the situation in two sentences and showed him the list of defects, he promptly got support from the manager.
			We only briefly showed her the wet interior of the vehicle.
			Since the car now really stank of cat urine, the lady could only stand being in it briefly.
			Half an hour and several phone calls later, she fortunately managed to organize a replacement vehicle for us.
			So we parked the two vehicles side by side and transferred everything from A to B.
			The lady apologized several more times and also recorded the remaining issues with the first vehicle. </p>
		<p> All in all, the whole operation took about 2 hours.
			Since it was now a humid 28 degrees, we were both ready for a shower.
			On the way to the campsite, we quickly got all the necessary food to make burgers in the evening. </p>
		<p> At the beautiful Big4 Coconut campsite, we met up again with the German couple we had met in Airlie Beach.
			We all decided to have burgers and end the evening with wine and other alcoholic drinks. </p>
